</div>

<div>
    <button id="show3" class="btn btn-primary btn-block" onclick="show3()">Compost</button>

   

    <div style="display:none" id="content3">
        <h4>The easiest way to make your own compost:</h4>
        <ol>
            <li>Get a area where you will grow your compost.</li>
            <li>Lay leaves for the bottom layer.</li>
            <li>The easiest part, throw your kitchen scraps on this pile, like egg shells, vegetables and coffee grounds.</li>
            <li>Next through grass cuttings.</li>
            <li>After a week or two of watering your compost, it will be ready to use in your garden for a healthier garden and enviroment.</li>
        </ol>
        <button id="less3" class="btn btn-danger btn-block" onclick="less3()">Less</button>
